All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    Board
    Class for board of Spectrangle game.
    Client
    Client class for use in Spectrangle game.
    ClientHandler
    ClientHandler class for use in Spectrangle game.
    Color
    Enumeration of the colors a tile's sides can have.
    ComputerPlayer
    Computer player class for playing the game according to a strategy.
    Field
    Field class for building a board and holding a placed tile.
    Game
    Class for controlling a Spectrangle game.
    HumanPlayer
    Human player controller for the game, mostly validating input from the console and parsing this to a move that is readable by the game.
    InvalidIndexException
    Exception for indexes outside the board.
    InvalidMoveException
    Exception for constructing moves using the wrong constructor.
    MarionettePlayer
    Marionette player is a class used by the server and the Client to keep track of players from connected Clients.
    Move
    Move class is used to store all relevant information for a move, such that it can be validated and placed afterwards.
    MoveType
    MoveType is used to distinguish between different moves the player can make.
    NaiveStrategy
    Naive strategy for computer player, makes a random valid move.
    Player
    Abstract player class for building players with.
    Protocol
    Centralized protocol definition to implement in the Client, ClientHandler and Server.
    Room
    Class for handling game rooms.
    RotatableTile
    RotatableTile is Tile that handles the rotation of a SimpleTile.
    Rotation
    Rotation based on the protocol.
    Server
    Server class for use in Spectrangle game.
    SimpleTile
    Simple Tile saves information about the colors and the points of a tile combined with the RotatableTile it achieves the full Tile functionality.
    SpectrangleBoardPrinter  
    Strategy
    Defines a strategy base interface for the computer player to implement.
    TilesBag
    TilesBag class for keeping track of the tiles that are not yet on the board or in a players hand.
